WEBVTT

01:15.275 --> 01:17.341
Smile, damn you.

01:17.343 --> 01:19.409
Smile!

01:22.847 --> 01:25.080
<i>[ Door opens ]</i> [ Gasps ]

01:32.189 --> 01:34.622
Shut the door.

01:34.624 --> 01:37.424
What do you want?

01:37.426 --> 01:40.593
I have a job for you.

01:40.595 --> 01:42.795
What kind of job?

01:42.797 --> 01:44.830
<i>It's heavy work.</i>

01:44.832 --> 01:47.866
Digging.
We'll need another man.

01:47.868 --> 01:52.836
- When do you want it done?
- Some night soon.

01:52.838 --> 01:54.804
Where?
<i>The graveyard.</i>

01:54.806 --> 01:58.473
Unless you're afraid.

02:00.643 --> 02:05.111
The job pays two dollars.
Take it or leave it.

02:05.113 --> 02:07.346
I'll take it.

02:09.149 --> 02:12.850
But the job pays three dollars.

02:12.852 --> 02:15.285
Unless you think
I deserve more.

02:15.287 --> 02:18.888
No. Three dollars
seems fair enough. Yep.

02:23.594 --> 02:26.161
[ Sighs,
gasps ]
<i>[ Clock chimes ]</i>

02:26.163 --> 02:30.564
[ Chiming ]

02:30.566 --> 02:33.466
[ Snoring ]

02:36.704 --> 02:41.606
¶¶ [ Humming ]

02:53.686 --> 02:56.420
And where do you think
you're going?

02:56.422 --> 02:59.523
Go back to sleep, sid.
I'm just runnin' away
from home.

02:59.525 --> 03:04.160
Again?
This time for sure.

03:05.863 --> 03:09.631
Me and Joe Harper
and Ben Rogers
is goin' to new Orleans...

03:09.633 --> 03:12.767
To be steamboat men.
Not if I tell
aunt Polly.

03:12.769 --> 03:14.802
[ Mumbling ]

03:14.804 --> 03:17.871
I knew you were gonna be
your annoying little self,
sid.

03:17.873 --> 03:20.607
So I rigged up
a little surprise for ya.

03:20.609 --> 03:23.209
There.
And so you don't get lonely...

03:26.314 --> 03:31.649
now, that right there
is the most poisonous spider
in the whole world.

03:31.651 --> 03:35.786
If you knock that glass over,
she's gonna be pretty angry.

03:35.788 --> 03:38.822
'Course, it could just be
a little harmless fruit spider.

03:38.824 --> 03:42.292
But, only one way
to find out, right?

04:23.301 --> 04:26.302
<i>[ Man ] Howdy, boys!</i>

04:26.304 --> 04:28.304
Hey, muff.
Yeah, hey, muff.

04:28.306 --> 04:30.506
Where are you headed
this hour of the night?

04:30.508 --> 04:32.941
We're runnin' away
from home.
<i>Uh-huh.</i>

04:32.943 --> 04:37.578
I used to do that all the time,
until home ran away from me.

04:37.580 --> 04:39.947
<i>Where'd they go?</i>

04:39.949 --> 04:42.582
As far away as they could.

04:43.551 --> 04:45.551
Come on.

04:45.553 --> 04:48.954
Don't let me stop you.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.957
Hey, when ya comin' back?

04:51.959 --> 04:54.025
Never!
Yep, never!

04:54.027 --> 04:56.327
Never, huh?

04:59.632 --> 05:02.566
See ya tomorrow.

05:25.490 --> 05:29.758
Bye, bye, Hannibal.
Good-bye! We're
gonna be steamboat men.

05:31.328 --> 05:34.929
Left and bring her
into the wind, Mr. Harper.
Aye, sir.

05:34.931 --> 05:37.331
Steady, now, steady.

05:37.333 --> 05:40.634
Steady it is, sir.

05:40.636 --> 05:44.471
Next stop, new Orleans.
Nothing can stop us
now.

05:49.977 --> 05:53.345
- Hard to port! Hard to port!
- What's port?

05:53.347 --> 05:56.047
To the left!
No, it's right!

05:56.049 --> 05:58.482
<i>To the right then.</i>
<i>Just pull it, Joe.</i>
<i>Pull it!</i>

05:58.484 --> 06:00.917
<i>Come on, Joe!</i>
<i>Pull!</i>

06:00.919 --> 06:03.486
[ Boys yelling ]

06:21.772 --> 06:24.405
[ Groans ]

06:24.407 --> 06:26.974
All right. Tom, tom.
Tom! Tom!

06:26.976 --> 06:30.110
<i>Tom!</i>

06:43.424 --> 06:45.557
[ Gagging ]

06:45.559 --> 06:48.660
[ Coughing ]

06:50.430 --> 06:52.897
<i>[ Joe and Ben ]</i>
<i>Tom! Tom!</i>

07:00.872 --> 07:04.840
You all right, tom?
Yeah, yeah.
Of course I'm all right.

07:04.842 --> 07:07.976
If it hadn't been for...

07:07.978 --> 07:11.079
Whoever it was,
you'd have been a goner.

07:11.081 --> 07:14.749
Town?
Town.
Come on.

07:31.834 --> 07:34.433
Bye, tom.

07:37.704 --> 07:40.103
[ Grunting ]

07:43.775 --> 07:46.709
<i>[ Thumping ]</i>

07:54.552 --> 07:57.119
[ Sighs ]
Mornin', everybody.
What's for breakfast?

07:57.121 --> 08:01.889
Well, you can start...
With this.

08:01.891 --> 08:04.691
<i>Eeow.</i>

08:04.693 --> 08:06.959
Couldn't I just have
some scrambled eggs?

08:06.961 --> 08:11.029
Tom, I have a notion
to skin you alive.

08:11.031 --> 08:14.098
Sneaking out 'til all hours!
Worrying a body to death!

08:14.100 --> 08:16.700
Yeah. Shall I get
the switch?

08:16.702 --> 08:21.471
I swore to your mama,
my own sister, on her deathbed
that I would raise you proper.

08:21.473 --> 08:23.806
And you're doin'
a fine job.
No.

08:23.808 --> 08:26.575
I know I am not doing
my duty by you.

08:26.577 --> 08:28.710
I'll get the switch.
No!

08:30.780 --> 08:35.816
I'll just be obliged
to make you work tomorrow.

08:35.818 --> 08:39.219
Tomorrow?
Couldn't I just take
a whippin'?

08:39.221 --> 08:42.889
I have got to do something,
and I ain't got the heart
to hit you.

08:42.890 --> 08:45.157
<i>Now sit.</i>

08:55.068 --> 08:57.601
<i>[ Chickens clucking ]</i>

09:31.769 --> 09:36.104
<i>[ Boy ] ¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

09:36.106 --> 09:40.141
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

09:40.143 --> 09:43.911
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

09:43.913 --> 09:47.114
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

09:47.116 --> 09:49.950
¶¶ [ whistling ] ¶ toot, toot ¶

09:49.952 --> 09:52.619
¶¶ [ whistling continues ]

09:52.621 --> 09:55.588
Are you feeling okay, tom?

09:55.590 --> 09:58.958
Hi, Billy.
I was havin' so much fun,
didn't even hear you comin'.

09:58.960 --> 10:02.027
Fun?
Whitewashin'
this here fence.

10:07.133 --> 10:12.535
Nah. That ain't fun.
That's work.

10:12.537 --> 10:15.838
Billy, if this was work,
would I be doin' it?

10:15.840 --> 10:19.741
Ain't every day
a boy gets
to whitewash a fence.

10:19.743 --> 10:22.276
Say, tom?
Hmm?

10:22.278 --> 10:25.912
Let me whitewash a little?

10:27.982 --> 10:31.016
Aunt Polly's awful particular
about this fence.

10:31.018 --> 10:33.051
<i>Just a little.</i>

10:33.053 --> 10:35.653
I'd like to help you out, bill.
Honest injun.

10:35.655 --> 10:38.589
But if you were to tackle
this here fence, and
anything was to happen to it...

10:38.591 --> 10:41.825
I'll be real careful.

10:42.694 --> 10:45.161
What'll you give me?

10:45.163 --> 10:47.062
Uhh...

11:25.268 --> 11:27.868
oop! Oooh!
[ Groans, coughs ]

11:28.670 --> 11:30.702
<i>Huck!</i>

11:34.274 --> 11:37.975
You're back!
Where'd you go?
Where've you been?

11:37.977 --> 11:40.644
Well, I'm a traveler.

11:40.646 --> 11:42.912
I go lots of places.

11:42.914 --> 11:46.115
Go upriver, downriver.
No place particular.

11:46.117 --> 11:49.751
I'm bound to pass through here
sometime.

11:51.721 --> 11:55.155
You're the one
who pulled me out
the other night.

11:56.925 --> 11:59.625
I felt like a swim.

11:59.627 --> 12:02.160
Come on.
I'll show you my place.

12:04.831 --> 12:07.965
So how long
you been livin' here,
huck?

12:07.967 --> 12:10.300
About a month.

12:10.302 --> 12:13.703
A month, huh?
Uh-huh.

12:13.705 --> 12:15.771
Well?

12:18.375 --> 12:21.309
Whoa!

12:24.180 --> 12:28.715
Last week, aunt Polly whupped me
for swipin' a pie that
was coolin' on the windowsill.

12:28.717 --> 12:31.984
<i>But it wasn't me.</i>
<i>Figured it was sid.</i>

12:31.986 --> 12:35.787
-He wanted it,
but I beat him to it.
-I oughta punch you in the nose.

12:38.358 --> 12:41.392
You're welcome to try.

12:41.394 --> 12:44.028
Maybe later.

12:46.098 --> 12:50.467
<i>So, when you're not</i>
<i>stealin' food and</i>
<i>savin' folks from drownin',</i>

12:50.469 --> 12:55.138
<i>what do you do</i>
<i>all day?</i>
Whatever I want.

12:58.810 --> 13:00.910
Sure are lucky.

13:00.912 --> 13:04.313
Yep.
I'm a free man.

13:07.184 --> 13:11.252
Go wherever I want when
I wanna go there, do whatever
I want when I want to do it.

13:11.254 --> 13:13.354
It's as simple as that.

13:14.824 --> 13:16.290
[ Snaps fingers ]

13:20.496 --> 13:22.529
It's good to see ya.

13:22.531 --> 13:24.564
What's that for?

13:24.566 --> 13:27.133
It's what friends do.

13:27.135 --> 13:29.268
We friends?

13:32.940 --> 13:36.441
It's up to you.

13:36.443 --> 13:38.943
If your aunt Polly
catches you and me,

13:38.945 --> 13:41.211
she'll whup you
from here to St. Louis.

13:41.213 --> 13:45.081
This has nothin' to do with her.
We was friends before.
Don't you remember?

13:45.083 --> 13:47.950
Yeah, I guess we were.

13:47.952 --> 13:50.585
Now we're friends again.

13:50.587 --> 13:53.053
Yeah, I guess we are.

13:55.991 --> 13:57.957
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>We won't do it again,</i>
<i>will we?</i>

13:57.959 --> 14:01.060
Will we?
I can't hear you.
Uh-uh.

14:06.233 --> 14:09.267
Thomas Sawyer!

14:09.269 --> 14:12.069
<i>Sorry I'm late for school,</i>
<i>Mr. dobbins.</i>

14:12.071 --> 14:16.173
Well, what's your excuse
this time?

14:16.175 --> 14:18.375
I stopped to talk
with huckleberry finn.

14:18.377 --> 14:20.610
[ Class gasping ]

14:20.612 --> 14:23.045
Thomas Sawyer!

14:23.047 --> 14:26.848
That is the most
astounding confession...

14:26.850 --> 14:29.350
I have ever had to listen to.

14:29.352 --> 14:32.419
Yes, sir.
<i>You are not unaware...</i>

14:32.421 --> 14:35.555
That it is forbidden
to converse with that...

14:35.557 --> 14:38.291
Idle wastrel?

14:38.293 --> 14:42.962
No, sir.
I-I mean, yes, sir.

14:42.964 --> 14:45.965
You know, of course,
that I shall have to punish you.
<i>Oh, no.</i>

14:45.967 --> 14:51.002
No, Mr. dobbins, please.
You wouldn't make me sit
with the girls.

14:51.004 --> 14:53.504
<i>[ Students giggling ]</i>

14:53.506 --> 14:56.139
Once again, Thomas Sawyer,

14:56.141 --> 14:59.608
you have outsmarted yourself.
[ Chuckling ]

15:00.611 --> 15:02.210
[ Giggling ]

15:02.212 --> 15:04.345
Ahh, ahh, ahh, ahh, ahh.

15:04.347 --> 15:06.947
<i>Grade seven's green book.</i>

15:06.949 --> 15:10.383
[ Moans ]

15:10.385 --> 15:14.620
<i>"A Missouri maiden's farewell</i>
<i>to Alabama."</i>

15:14.622 --> 15:18.957
<i>"Alabama, good-bye.</i>
<i>I love thee well.</i>

15:18.959 --> 15:22.593
<i>"For, yes, for a while</i>
<i>do I leave thee now.</i>

15:22.595 --> 15:24.962
<i>"Sad? Yes.</i>

15:24.964 --> 15:27.898
<i>"Sad thoughts of thee</i>
<i>my heart doth swell...</i>

15:27.900 --> 15:31.534
<i>"And burning recollections</i>
<i>from my brow.</i>

15:31.536 --> 15:34.303
<i>"For I have wandered through...</i>

15:34.305 --> 15:37.606
<i>"Thy flowery woods.</i>

15:37.608 --> 15:41.610
<i>"Have roamed and read here</i>
<i>tallapoosa's stream.</i>

15:41.612 --> 15:44.613
<i>Have listened</i>
<i>to Tallahassee's... "</i>

15:44.615 --> 15:48.583
[ bell ringing ]
<i>[ Mr. dobbins ]</i>
<i>who belongs to this peach?</i>

15:48.585 --> 15:53.487
<i>Becky Thatcher,</i>
<i>do you belong to this peach?</i>

15:53.489 --> 15:59.459
<i>You will not abandon</i>
<i>unconsumed food in my school.</i>
<i>Do you hear?</i>

16:25.052 --> 16:27.152
Whoa!
<i>[ Water splashes ]</i>

16:35.228 --> 16:39.063
Whew!
Hello, huck.

16:39.065 --> 16:41.732
Hello, yourself,
and see how you like it.

16:43.368 --> 16:45.701
Whatcha doin' here?

16:45.703 --> 16:48.236
<i>Lookin' for jackasses.</i>

16:48.238 --> 16:50.304
Under a bridge?

16:50.306 --> 16:54.340
I found one, didn't I?
[ Laughing ]
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

16:56.110 --> 16:59.111
You gonna let her
do that to you?

16:59.113 --> 17:01.613
It's 'cause she likes me.

17:01.615 --> 17:06.215
She pushes you off a bridge
'cause she likes you?
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

17:07.752 --> 17:11.019
I think you're both crazy.

17:12.055 --> 17:14.989
Hey, huck, what you got
in the sack?

17:14.991 --> 17:17.590
A dead cat.

17:17.593 --> 17:20.760
Wagon run over him.
Guts come out both ends.

17:20.762 --> 17:24.997
[ Coughs ]
What's a dead cat
good for?

17:24.999 --> 17:27.299
To cure warts with.

17:27.300 --> 17:30.602
I got one.
How's it work?

17:30.604 --> 17:34.305
You take your dead cat
to the graveyard on the day
somebody wicked's been buried.

17:34.307 --> 17:37.474
When the devil comes,
you heave your dead cat at him
and say,

17:37.476 --> 17:40.610
"devil follow corpse.
Cat follow devil.

17:40.612 --> 17:43.212
Warts follow cat.
I'm done with you."

17:43.214 --> 17:46.048
That'll fetch any wart.
<i>Sounds right.</i>

17:46.050 --> 17:49.484
- So when you gonna try?
- Tonight.

17:49.486 --> 17:52.420
Let me go with ya, huck.

17:53.689 --> 17:55.755
You might get scared.

17:55.757 --> 18:00.059
I ain't scared of nothin'.

18:00.061 --> 18:05.164
<i>[ Wolf howling ]</i>

18:15.375 --> 18:18.376
<i>[ Muff making eerie sounds ]</i>

18:18.378 --> 18:21.345
Dead seems kinda lively tonight,
don't they?

18:21.347 --> 18:24.214
Baah!

18:24.216 --> 18:26.583
<i>[ Doc Robinson ] Be careful!</i>

18:32.490 --> 18:34.690
Hmm.

18:34.692 --> 18:38.360
[ Mumbling ]

18:38.362 --> 18:42.197
<i>[ Huck ] Who are they?</i>
<i>[ Tom ] the two on the right</i>
<i>ain't so bad.</i>

18:42.199 --> 18:46.067
<i>The skinny one's doc Robinson,</i>
<i>and the fat one's muff Potter.</i>

18:46.069 --> 18:51.238
<i>Muff wouldn't hurt a fly.</i>
<i>That third fellow there?</i>

18:51.240 --> 18:54.507
That's injun Joe.
Injun Joe?

18:54.509 --> 18:57.643
You know him?

18:57.645 --> 19:00.212
Let's just say I met him once,

19:00.214 --> 19:02.714
and I ain't in a hurry
to meet him again.

19:05.752 --> 19:09.119
They're goin' for
one of them old graves.

19:11.790 --> 19:15.424
[ Grunting ]

19:15.426 --> 19:18.126
[ Shovel thumping ]

19:18.128 --> 19:20.161
[ Doc whispering ]
That's it. That's it.

19:20.163 --> 19:22.296
W-would it be all right...

19:22.298 --> 19:26.866
If we stopped for a...
A little libation?

19:26.868 --> 19:30.636
What?
I need me a drink.

19:30.638 --> 19:34.172
No! Haul it up!
And hurry.

19:39.878 --> 19:44.680
<i>Yep! C'mon, c'mon.</i>
<i>Pry it open. Tip it over.</i>

19:49.886 --> 19:51.886
Murrell!

19:51.888 --> 19:56.290
One-eyed murrell?
My God!
[ Chuckles ]

20:05.500 --> 20:09.168
Put the coffin back.
Cover up your tracks.

20:11.505 --> 20:15.273
Hey, not so fast.
Get your hands
off me.

20:15.275 --> 20:19.743
Gimme that box.
Doc, Joe, let's talk
this over like gentle...

20:20.879 --> 20:24.146
what'd you do that for?
That's just not right.

20:24.148 --> 20:26.214
Is it, doc?
Come here.

20:26.216 --> 20:29.417
<i>Come on, now.</i>
<i>I got ya.</i>
It's a treasure map.

20:29.419 --> 20:32.219
<i>Oh!</i>
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

20:32.221 --> 20:36.622
Murrell's treasure?
Murrell's lost treasure?

20:36.624 --> 20:39.324
By glory, we're rich!

20:39.326 --> 20:41.426
<i>[ Doc ] It's mine!</i>

20:41.428 --> 20:42.794
Oooh!

20:53.772 --> 20:56.372
[ Groaning ] No.

20:59.443 --> 21:03.711
<i>[ Doc whimpering ]</i>

21:10.486 --> 21:14.887
[ Mumbling ]
What are you doing
with that thing?

21:14.889 --> 21:17.723
[ Doc groaning ]

21:55.929 --> 21:58.963
We gotta tell
the sheriff.
<i>I ain't tellin' nobody.</i>

21:58.965 --> 22:01.899
Unless you're dumber than
I think you are, you're gonna
keep your mouth shut too.

22:01.901 --> 22:03.901
But we seen a murder.

22:03.903 --> 22:06.803
Yeah. And there's gonna be
two more murders
if we squeak on injun Joe.

22:06.805 --> 22:10.839
Killin' us
would mean less to him
than drowning a few cats.

22:13.777 --> 22:18.746
[ Panting ]
I guess you're right.
We can't tell nobody.

22:20.382 --> 22:22.648
You're damn right.

22:22.650 --> 22:25.884
Just to make sure
you don't change your mind,

22:25.886 --> 22:28.553
we're gonna swear an oath.

22:28.555 --> 22:32.356
We'll write it down
and sign it in blood.

22:32.358 --> 22:34.725
Our blood?

22:34.727 --> 22:39.396
Unless you wanna go back
and borrow some
from doc Robinson.

22:43.468 --> 22:47.469
You do it.
I ain't much good
at writin'.

22:48.872 --> 22:51.839
Damn!
I lost my marble!

22:51.841 --> 22:54.508
We've got bigger things
to worry about.

22:54.510 --> 22:57.611
Now, would you please
write this down?

22:57.613 --> 23:01.314
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.

23:05.653 --> 23:10.555
Huck finn and tom Sawyer...

23:10.557 --> 23:12.757
Swear they'll keep shut...

23:12.759 --> 23:15.493
<i>About what they seen.</i>

23:15.495 --> 23:19.830
May they drop down dead
if they ever tell a soul.

23:21.867 --> 23:24.068
And rot.

23:25.004 --> 23:27.470
And rot.

23:29.807 --> 23:32.908
Now we sign it.

24:07.744 --> 24:10.644
"H" is for huck.

24:12.681 --> 24:15.748
"F" for finn.

24:15.750 --> 24:17.950
Thanks.

24:23.156 --> 24:27.158
<i>[ Thunderclaps ]</i>

24:57.923 --> 25:01.758
I'm gonna kill you, tom Sawyer.

25:01.760 --> 25:04.627
[ Growling ]

25:04.629 --> 25:06.795
No-o-o!

25:06.797 --> 25:08.863
No!

25:08.865 --> 25:11.498
[ Panting ]

25:11.500 --> 25:13.700
Bad dream?

25:13.702 --> 25:19.004
Ow! Mother, mother!
Tom hit me with a pillow!

25:19.006 --> 25:21.206
<i>[ Excited chatting ]</i>

25:21.208 --> 25:24.108
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>C'mon! C'mon!</i>
<i>Right down here.</i>

25:28.047 --> 25:31.715
<i>Hey, tom!</i>
<i>School's been called off.</i>

25:31.717 --> 25:35.551
Why? What for?
There's been
a murder.

25:39.056 --> 25:41.890
I didn't do it!
I swear, I didn't do it!

25:41.892 --> 25:46.160
What happened to your face?
I-I-I don't know, but
I swear I didn't do it.

25:46.162 --> 25:49.163
Look what I found!
It's muff Potter's knife.

25:49.165 --> 25:53.100
I sold it to him last winter.
<i>I say lynch him.</i>
<i>Lynch him now!</i>

25:53.102 --> 25:55.202
- You've gotta believe me!
- No.

25:55.204 --> 25:58.805
<i>- [ Injun Joe ]</i>
<i>I saw the murder.</i>
- [ Crowd ] Hang him up.

25:59.874 --> 26:04.809
<i>Oh. Oh, Joe.</i>
<i>Thank the lord.</i>

26:04.811 --> 26:07.645
You tell them now.

26:07.647 --> 26:12.016
You tell them...
you tell them it ain't me.

26:12.018 --> 26:14.952
<i>[ Sheriff ]</i>
<i>Tell us what you know.</i>

26:16.021 --> 26:19.155
Yeah, I passed through here
last night.

26:19.157 --> 26:23.292
And I saw muff
and doc Robinson...
Diggin' up that there grave.

26:23.294 --> 26:25.160
[ Crowd mumbling ]

26:25.162 --> 26:29.898
<i>Then in a drunken rage,</i>
<i>i saw muff stab the doc.</i>

26:29.900 --> 26:32.934
[ Crowd yelling ]
String him up!

26:32.936 --> 26:37.238
That ain't
the way it happened.
I swear.

26:37.240 --> 26:41.742
We found the map...
To murrell's treasure.

26:41.744 --> 26:46.346
And then Joe and doc
got to fightin'.
Murrell's treasure.

26:46.348 --> 26:49.916
You hear that, people?
More drunk talk
from muff Potter.

26:49.918 --> 26:54.053
Murrell's lost treasure
is an old wives' tale.

26:54.055 --> 26:56.889
I know the history
of this entire county,

26:56.891 --> 26:59.291
and I'm telling you
it doesn't exist.

26:59.293 --> 27:02.861
But I seen the map!

27:02.863 --> 27:05.897
I say you're lyin'.

27:05.899 --> 27:09.133
I say there ain't no map.

27:09.135 --> 27:12.903
- And there never was.
<i>- [ Man ] String him up!</i>

27:14.773 --> 27:17.673
Who all thinks muff Potter's
a drunk,

27:17.675 --> 27:21.943
a liar and a murderer,
raise your hand!

27:21.945 --> 27:23.978
[ Shouting ]

27:23.980 --> 27:27.113
<i>I say we hang him!</i>

27:30.751 --> 27:35.253
<i>All right, folks.</i>
<i>Let's just hold on here.</i>
<i>Now, hold on.</i>

27:35.255 --> 27:37.355
Thank you.

27:39.158 --> 27:43.260
Now, you folks
wouldn't be trying to deny me
the pleasure...

27:43.262 --> 27:46.962
Of presidin' over a trial,
now would ya?

27:48.131 --> 27:51.365
You all right,
Mr. Potter?

27:51.367 --> 27:54.801
After all, what would be
the point of having
a new judge in town...

27:54.803 --> 27:58.037
If you won't let me
judge anything?
<i>We all know he's guilty!</i>

27:58.039 --> 28:02.374
Ow! Hey!
We all know you're
an idiot, ed dobbins.

28:02.376 --> 28:05.110
Listen to me,
you pointy-headed ghouls.

28:05.112 --> 28:08.379
Muff Potter may be
the scum of the earth,

28:08.381 --> 28:11.715
but he deserves a fair trial,
and I aim to see he gets one.

28:11.717 --> 28:14.417
<i>Judge, how soon can you</i>
<i>get this business started?</i>

28:14.419 --> 28:16.685
I should be able
to start hearin' evidence
day after tomorrow.

28:16.687 --> 28:22.123
Settled. Now,
the rest of you <i> good</i> citizens,
you be on your way.

28:22.125 --> 28:24.925
Let the law do its job.
Come on.

28:24.927 --> 28:28.228
Let's go, muff.

28:35.837 --> 28:39.871
I didn't do it, tom.
I swear, I didn't do it.

28:41.741 --> 28:46.977
<i>[ Children ]</i>
<i>¶ there's gonna be a hanging</i>
<i>there's gonna be a hanging ¶</i>

28:52.016 --> 28:54.216
<i>you wanna drop dead and rot?</i>

28:54.218 --> 28:57.752
Muff's innocent, huck.
We gotta help him.

28:57.754 --> 29:00.454
We ain't gotta do nothin'.

29:02.024 --> 29:04.457
You'd let him hang
for somethin' he didn't do?

29:04.459 --> 29:08.093
It ain't no skin off my back.

29:08.095 --> 29:10.428
What if we could get the map?

29:10.430 --> 29:14.198
We could prove muff
was tellin' the truth, and it
wouldn't make us break our oath.

29:14.200 --> 29:18.035
Only one little problem.
That map is in
injun Joe's pocket.

29:18.037 --> 29:21.338
Well, if you're scared...
why should I stick my neck out
for muff Potter?

29:21.340 --> 29:23.773
'Cause we know
he didn't do it.
So?

29:23.775 --> 29:28.010
So not doin' anything
about it is wrong.
Says who?

29:28.012 --> 29:30.045
[ Sighs ]

29:30.047 --> 29:32.781
What if it was you
in muff's shoes?
It ain't.

29:32.783 --> 29:36.384
What if it was me?
If you was that stupid,

29:36.386 --> 29:39.887
maybe you'd deserve
what was comin' to you.

29:39.889 --> 29:42.155
It's not what friends do, huck.

29:43.391 --> 29:45.824
I thought we was friends.

29:46.927 --> 29:50.028
Maybe I don't know
what you're talkin' about.

29:55.134 --> 29:58.735
¶¶ [ Humming ]

30:02.774 --> 30:05.775
Hello, tom.
Hey, Becky.

30:05.777 --> 30:08.344
Sorry I pushed you
in the creek yesterday.

30:08.346 --> 30:11.046
You can push me in
if you want to.

30:11.048 --> 30:15.783
I would.
I just don't feel like it
right now.

30:17.486 --> 30:19.986
Thank you.

30:25.293 --> 30:27.760
What's the matter, tom?

30:27.762 --> 30:30.529
Oh, nothin'.

30:33.967 --> 30:36.467
You can tell me.
[ Sighs ]

30:36.469 --> 30:40.237
I won't ever tell anybody.

30:43.242 --> 30:46.209
[ Sighs ]

30:46.211 --> 30:48.244
Here.

30:50.248 --> 30:52.881
This is for you.

30:54.117 --> 30:56.216
Thanks.

30:58.987 --> 31:01.354
You ever been engaged, Becky?

31:01.356 --> 31:04.190
No.
How do you do it?

31:05.393 --> 31:09.361
Well, you gotta tell the person
that you love 'im.

31:10.430 --> 31:12.463
Then what?

31:14.033 --> 31:16.333
Well, then you're 'spose
to kiss.

31:16.335 --> 31:19.869
Really?
Sure.

31:21.939 --> 31:26.474
You first.
I love you. There.
Now you gotta say it to me.

31:26.476 --> 31:29.877
Turn your face away.

31:29.879 --> 31:34.314
And you can't tell anybody
ever.
I won't.

31:37.385 --> 31:40.084
I love you.

31:42.888 --> 31:47.590
Well, I...
Guess everything's done
but the kissin' part.

31:54.431 --> 31:56.230
[ Gasps ]

31:56.232 --> 31:58.432
Here.

31:59.501 --> 32:03.603
Oh, tom, it's, it's...
what is it?

32:03.605 --> 32:07.907
It's your engagement ring.
It's beautiful.

32:07.909 --> 32:11.076
It sure is.
Why, when I was engaged
to Amy Lawrence, she...

32:11.078 --> 32:14.279
what? You mean,
I'm not the first?

32:14.281 --> 32:17.915
Yeah. But, Becky,
that was ages ago.
Two months at least.

32:17.917 --> 32:19.917
I hate you.
What?

32:19.919 --> 32:23.120
I hate you, and I hope you die!

32:25.491 --> 32:28.191
What'd I do?

32:43.474 --> 32:49.143
[ Boy ]
Guys, that's injun Joe.
Run!

32:49.145 --> 32:52.646
This here belong to any of you?

32:57.485 --> 33:00.085
Hah!
[ Gasps ]

33:31.050 --> 33:34.351
Uh, anybody come to see me,
sheriff?
Muff, don't be stupid.

33:34.353 --> 33:37.153
Nobody cares about you.
Nobody's gonna miss you
when you're gone.

33:37.155 --> 33:40.221
<i>[ Sheriff ] Here you go.</i>

33:43.993 --> 33:47.394
Thank you.

33:47.396 --> 33:49.696
[ Clears throat ]

33:53.435 --> 33:55.568
[ Sighs ]

34:09.683 --> 34:12.617
Injun Joe's on the move.

34:19.291 --> 34:22.058
What made you come back, huck?

34:22.060 --> 34:25.462
I figured if you did it alone,
you'd probably splotch it up.

34:25.464 --> 34:27.697
<i>Yeah, probably.</i>

34:35.472 --> 34:38.806
<i>[ Man snoring ]</i>

34:45.213 --> 34:47.413
<i>[ Snoring continues ]</i>

34:47.415 --> 34:50.282
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>You better watch your mouth.</i>

34:50.284 --> 34:52.350
<i>[ Arguing, fighting ]</i>

34:52.351 --> 34:56.420
[ Arguing, chatting ]

35:12.337 --> 35:14.570
<i>[ Injun Joe ]</i>
<i>Some kid dropped a marble</i>
<i>in the graveyard.</i>

35:14.572 --> 35:17.805
You see this here?
He's got my marble.

35:20.342 --> 35:22.175
Agh!

35:33.821 --> 35:37.255
Eh, probably a drunk.

35:38.491 --> 35:41.892
It ain't
muff Potter.
[ Laughing ]
It's so.

35:41.894 --> 35:46.429
The only stumblin'
he's gonna be doin'
is at the end of a rope.

35:47.665 --> 35:49.665
Shut up, [ Clears throat ]

35:49.667 --> 35:51.733
Partner.

35:51.735 --> 35:54.569
Yeah, Joe...
Partner.

35:55.605 --> 35:57.638
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Come on, move!</i>
<i>Let's move.</i>

35:57.640 --> 36:00.807
<i>Watch it. Watch it.</i>
<i>C'mon, hit me.</i>

36:00.809 --> 36:03.476
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

36:05.513 --> 36:08.847
<i>Nice little pirogue</i>
<i>you got there.</i>

36:13.687 --> 36:16.187
<i>Come on, lefty.</i>
<i>All right, lefty.</i>

36:16.189 --> 36:19.924
<i>Get it out.</i>
<i>That's it, that's it.</i>

36:19.926 --> 36:22.459
[ Man ]
Double hold.
Now, c'mon.

36:22.461 --> 36:25.395
All right,
separate apart.
Go ahead.

36:26.798 --> 36:30.266
I guess we can use muff's raft.

36:30.268 --> 36:33.269
Yeah.
I doubt he'll be usin' it
anytime soon.

36:33.271 --> 36:36.438
We better hide the raft
and camp out
'til first light.

36:53.422 --> 36:56.222
[ Bird squawking ]

37:09.670 --> 37:11.803
Huck?

37:16.575 --> 37:18.708
Huck?

37:22.946 --> 37:25.212
Huck?

37:26.548 --> 37:28.614
Huck!

37:38.258 --> 37:40.358
[ Laughing ]

37:52.805 --> 37:56.006
[ Snoring ]

38:09.954 --> 38:12.854
He's just drunk asleep.

38:12.856 --> 38:15.723
Shouldn't be too hard
to get that map.

38:15.725 --> 38:18.492
Yeah. Let's get it
and "git."

38:18.494 --> 38:21.694
<i>[ Snoring continues ]</i>

38:24.298 --> 38:26.531
Ain't ya comin'?

38:26.533 --> 38:29.800
One map don't need
the two of us.

38:29.802 --> 38:33.537
I'll wait here.

38:33.539 --> 38:36.973
[ Snoring ]

38:39.811 --> 38:41.744
[ Twig cracks ]

38:41.746 --> 38:43.512
[ Gasps ]

38:53.957 --> 38:56.457
[ Groans ]

38:57.560 --> 39:00.961
[ Sighs ]

39:00.963 --> 39:04.864
<i>[ Snoring continues ]</i> Go.

39:15.075 --> 39:17.708
[ Snorts ]

39:36.861 --> 39:38.694
[ Sneezes ]

39:38.696 --> 39:43.565
[ Pots crashing ]

39:55.778 --> 39:59.979
Them goddamn wild boars.

39:59.981 --> 40:02.614
Hah!

40:14.894 --> 40:17.895
[ Sighs ]

40:17.897 --> 40:20.597
You had to sneeze.

40:23.835 --> 40:27.870
<i>[ Thunderclaps ]</i>
Muff's raft must've
washed away in the storm.

40:27.872 --> 40:32.441
I guess we'll have to take
the long way back
to Hannibal.

40:32.443 --> 40:35.444
But I'll tell ya,
your ol' aunt's gonna tar
the head off of you...

40:35.446 --> 40:38.980
If she finds out
you've been out with me
all this time.

40:39.716 --> 40:42.016
What?

40:42.985 --> 40:45.552
It's the old
haunted house.
So?

40:45.554 --> 40:49.689
Ghosts don't come out
'til night anyway.
[ Sniffling ]

40:49.691 --> 40:53.159
<i>[ Clanking ]</i>
Then what was that?

40:53.161 --> 40:55.761
I don't know,
but it's gettin' closer.

40:55.763 --> 40:58.864
Then what are we
standing here for?

41:11.811 --> 41:15.612
<i>[ Door creaking ]</i>

41:38.136 --> 41:41.036
<i>Tom. Tom.</i>

41:58.955 --> 42:02.823
<i>[ Creaking ]</i> What was that?

42:02.825 --> 42:05.559
They say this place is haunted.

42:05.561 --> 42:08.828
Ahh!
With rats maybe.

42:08.830 --> 42:11.564
<i>[ Creaking continues ]</i>

42:11.566 --> 42:13.499
<i>[ Injun Joe ] Let's go to work.</i>

42:15.069 --> 42:17.235
According to murrell's map,

42:17.237 --> 42:21.872
it should be
right next to the fireplace.

42:41.526 --> 42:44.660
<i>[ Injun Joe ]</i>
<i>Hey, dig faster,</i>
<i>you stinkin' hog.</i>

42:44.662 --> 42:46.662
<i>I'm doin' all the work.</i>

42:46.664 --> 42:51.098
That's a damn lie!
I'm diggin' like
a chick on the beach.

42:51.100 --> 42:53.233
Move over.
Ahh!

42:53.235 --> 42:55.968
<i>Quit your bellyachin' and dig.</i>

42:59.239 --> 43:04.075
<i>[ Emmett ] You sure</i>
<i>about the fireplace?</i>
<i>Ain't that what I said?</i>

43:05.912 --> 43:08.712
<i>[ Emmett ]</i>
<i>Well, if it's the right place,</i>
<i>he sure buried it deep.</i>

43:08.714 --> 43:12.549
- I'm halfway to China.
<i>- Just keep diggin'.</i>

43:17.922 --> 43:21.256
You see?
Right here.

43:21.258 --> 43:23.725
<i>Fireplace!</i>

43:23.727 --> 43:27.628
I think I found somethin'.
Great snakes!

43:30.532 --> 43:33.766
[ Screaming ]

43:33.768 --> 43:37.703
<i>[ Screaming ]</i>
<i>I gotta get outta here!</i>

43:37.705 --> 43:40.105
<i>[ Screaming continues ]</i>

43:46.012 --> 43:48.245
<i>Shut up!</i>

43:58.289 --> 44:01.690
You screamin' coward.

44:01.692 --> 44:05.560
<i>That wasn't ghosts.</i>
<i>It was cobwebs!</i>

44:05.562 --> 44:07.828
Now, c'mon!

44:07.830 --> 44:10.897
<i>[ Emmett ]</i>
<i>Well, no need to hit me.</i>

44:17.338 --> 44:20.939
[ Grunting ] God, that's heavy!

44:23.076 --> 44:26.844
Go ahead and knock it off.
Quick.

44:26.846 --> 44:30.247
<i>[ Gasping ]</i>
<i>Good lord! Look at you.</i>

44:30.249 --> 44:33.817
<i>You beautiful money.</i>

44:33.819 --> 44:36.885
Hello, Texas and the good life.

44:38.355 --> 44:40.254
<i>No!</i>

44:40.256 --> 44:42.623
<i>What?</i>
We'll wait.

44:42.625 --> 44:45.325
<i>'Til after the trial.</i>
<i>I've got to testify.</i>

44:45.327 --> 44:48.828
Make sure muff takes the blame
for doc's murder.

44:48.830 --> 44:54.066
- Where're we gonna keep it
in the meantime?
- Number two under the cross.

44:54.068 --> 44:58.303
<i>Load up. I've got some things</i>
<i>to take care of in town.</i>
Number two under the cross.

45:00.040 --> 45:05.977
[ Emmett grunting ]
Look who's doin'
all the darn work.

45:05.979 --> 45:09.246
<i>Raining like pouring pigs</i>
<i>on a rawhide. Well...</i>

45:25.930 --> 45:28.030
no more map.

45:28.032 --> 45:30.766
No more muff.

45:37.707 --> 45:39.807
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>Number two under the cross.</i>

45:39.809 --> 45:44.711
<i>[ Huck ] If you ask me,</i>
<i>we're better off not knowin'.</i>
<i>Why?</i>

45:44.713 --> 45:48.281
<i>Why?</i>
<i>'Cause we're pushin' our luck</i>
<i>messin' with injun Joe.</i>

45:48.283 --> 45:52.285
It's the best way I know of
to get killed.

45:52.287 --> 45:56.422
Yeah. They say
he's the best knife fighter
on the whole Mississippi.

45:56.424 --> 45:59.825
No.
My pap's the best.

45:59.827 --> 46:03.128
Taught injun Joe
everything he knows.

46:03.130 --> 46:06.297
Your pap knew injun Joe?

46:06.299 --> 46:08.832
They met in jail.

46:08.834 --> 46:14.002
See, my pap was always runnin'
from the law, 'cept when he was
beatin' me like a rented mule.

46:15.306 --> 46:19.474
Anyways, he taught Joe
how to throw a knife.

46:50.005 --> 46:53.206
He taught me too.

46:53.208 --> 46:55.308
<i>[ Bell ringing ]</i>

46:56.878 --> 47:01.346
<i>[ Ringing continues ]</i>

47:01.348 --> 47:03.815
Huck, you hear that?

47:03.817 --> 47:06.417
<i>[ Ringing continues ]</i>

47:06.419 --> 47:08.485
Them's church bells.

47:08.487 --> 47:11.955
Nah.
It ain't Sunday.
Oh.

47:11.957 --> 47:14.524
Them's funeral bells.

47:14.526 --> 47:17.326
You're right.

47:21.165 --> 47:23.131
<i>[ Joe ]</i>
<i>He sold it to Doug Tanner...</i>
<i>no, wait.</i>

47:23.133 --> 47:26.367
<i>Mickey Douglas got the marble</i>
<i>from his cousin in St. Louis...</i>

47:26.369 --> 47:31.071
Who traded it to Alfred temple,
who sold it to...
Johnny Miller.

47:31.073 --> 47:35.208
No, wait.
Alfred sold it to...
[ Grunting ]

47:35.210 --> 47:38.844
Just tell me
who owned it last, boy.
Tom Sawyer owned it last.

47:38.846 --> 47:43.514
But it don't matter now
'cause now tom's dead.

47:43.516 --> 47:46.216
That's too bad.

47:46.218 --> 47:48.251
I'm so sad.

47:50.455 --> 47:53.222
Yeah, that's it.
Run, fat boy.

47:53.224 --> 47:55.290
Run!

47:57.460 --> 48:00.093
Tom Sawyer's hat.

48:02.297 --> 48:06.098
They found it in the wreckage
of muff Potter's boat.

48:06.100 --> 48:10.435
The mighty Mississippi
claims another life.

48:12.172 --> 48:15.873
<i>And while there's some comfort</i>
<i>in knowing...</i>

48:15.875 --> 48:17.541
<i>Tom's fate,</i>

48:19.578 --> 48:23.212
<i>- he was so young, just a boy.</i>
<i>- Hey, that's my hat.</i>

48:23.214 --> 48:26.248
<i>And a good boy.</i>
It's me.

48:26.250 --> 48:29.584
[ Laughs ]
They think I'm dead.
Can you believe it?

48:29.586 --> 48:33.287
<i>Boy, this is the best trick</i>
<i>that's ever been played</i>
<i>in the history of Hannibal ever.</i>

48:33.289 --> 48:36.556
They actually miss me.
What do you think of that?

48:36.558 --> 48:41.260
I don't know.
I ain't never been missed.
<i>[ Becky ] I can't believe it.</i>

48:41.262 --> 48:45.564
<i>I can't believe he's gone.</i>
<i>I wish I could see him</i>
<i>just one more time.</i>

48:45.566 --> 48:48.366
I'd tell him
I love him.
[ Gasps ]

48:48.368 --> 48:50.634
<i>And I'd hold him close,</i>
<i>and I'd kiss him...</i>

48:50.636 --> 48:54.270
Right in front of everybody.

48:54.272 --> 48:57.640
Hey,
I'm still here.
Huck!

48:57.642 --> 49:00.109
<i>[ Judge ]</i>
<i>...His spirit,</i>

49:00.111 --> 49:02.978
<i>a bit mischievous.</i>

49:05.082 --> 49:09.150
We have to admit, there's
a little bit of tom Sawyer
in all of us.

49:11.521 --> 49:14.154
I know I speak for everyone
when I say...

49:14.156 --> 49:16.623
I am going to miss him.

49:16.625 --> 49:19.626
<i>[ Mourners weeping ]</i>
I'm beginnin'
to miss me too.

49:19.628 --> 49:25.231
<i>To accept this loss...</i>
how long you gonna make
your aunt suffer?

49:25.233 --> 49:27.933
What are you talkin' about?

49:27.935 --> 49:29.935
Look.

49:29.937 --> 49:32.103
[ Crying ]

49:32.105 --> 49:36.073
She does look kinda sad,
doesn't she?

49:36.075 --> 49:39.142
[ Sobbing ]
<i>Aunt Polly,</i>
<i>please don't cry.</i>

49:39.144 --> 49:42.145
You got all these people
bawling their eyes out
for ya.

49:42.147 --> 49:46.015
Go home, tom.
<i>[ Judge ]</i>
<i>Lord, we'd give anything...</i>

49:46.017 --> 49:49.952
To have tom back with us
right now.

49:49.954 --> 49:52.087
<i>Amen.</i>

49:55.358 --> 49:58.058
[ Chatting in amazement ]

49:59.361 --> 50:01.728
<i>[ Woman ] It's tom Sawyer!</i>

50:01.730 --> 50:05.064
[ Laughs ]

50:06.967 --> 50:10.401
Tom! Tom!
Oh, tom!

50:17.576 --> 50:19.642
Hello, Becky.

50:23.314 --> 50:27.115
Becky Thatcher!

50:28.751 --> 50:31.451
<i>Now that you're alive again,</i>
<i>tom Sawyer,</i>

50:31.453 --> 50:34.987
you should set your mind
to being useful.

50:34.989 --> 50:37.456
A young man doesn't want
to waste his time...

50:37.458 --> 50:42.059
<i>Foolin' folks and</i>
<i>fallin' out of church ceilings.</i>

50:45.230 --> 50:47.763
She is absolutely right.

50:47.765 --> 50:50.499
Come on.
We're going home.
Ow! Ow!

50:50.501 --> 50:55.437
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>Aunt Polly, I just fell</i>
<i>15 feet onto a hard floor. Ow!</i>

50:58.275 --> 51:00.275
<i>I don't say it wasn't</i>
<i>a fine joke, tom.</i>

51:00.277 --> 51:02.610
<i>But to keep everybody suffering</i>
<i>while you had a good time!</i>

51:02.612 --> 51:05.312
Hang you, tom!
Can't you
ever learn anything?

51:05.314 --> 51:09.082
I've a mind to having you
whitewashin' the whole town
for what you did.

51:09.084 --> 51:11.784
Shall I get
some more soap, mother?

51:13.354 --> 51:16.655
I don't know why
you're smilin', sid.
You're next!

51:16.657 --> 51:19.157
Ahh.

51:30.103 --> 51:33.471
<i>[ Clinking noise ]</i>

51:34.640 --> 51:38.174
Huck,
whatcha doin'?
I'm packing.

51:38.176 --> 51:40.576
What for?

51:40.578 --> 51:44.346
It's time to move
on down the river.
Why?

51:44.348 --> 51:48.350
Why? 'Cause it's what I do.
I never stay long in one place.
I gotta keep movin'.

51:48.352 --> 51:52.220
What about muff Potter?
We tried.
It didn't work out.

51:52.222 --> 51:55.456
But the trial's tomorrow,
huck. But, huck...

51:55.458 --> 51:58.091
look! I don't leave places
'cause I want to.

51:58.093 --> 52:02.428
I leave 'cause sooner or later
they're gonna find me
and run me out.

52:02.430 --> 52:07.165
I'm sick and tired of it, tom.
I'm gonna beat 'em
to the punch this time.

52:10.503 --> 52:14.104
I thought we was friends, huck.

52:15.107 --> 52:17.340
You thought wrong.

52:17.342 --> 52:20.843
I ain't got no friends.
I ain't got time for 'em.

52:20.845 --> 52:26.114
<i>But if I did have one,</i>
<i>I'd want him to be like you.</i>

52:32.788 --> 52:34.487
Hah!

52:34.489 --> 52:36.188
[ Gasps ]

52:37.457 --> 52:39.290
[ Coughs ]

52:53.372 --> 52:55.438
<i>You lose something?</i>

52:59.477 --> 53:01.710
It... it ain't mine.

53:01.712 --> 53:04.379
Don't you lie to me, boy!

53:04.381 --> 53:09.350
You know that is my marble.
Reason I didn't recognize it...

53:09.352 --> 53:11.484
<i>Is I lost it</i>
<i>two, three months ago</i>
<i>in a graveyard.</i>

53:14.322 --> 53:17.423
<i>Now...</i>

53:17.425 --> 53:19.824
Fetch me the knife.

53:22.261 --> 53:24.828
I said, fetch!

53:37.609 --> 53:40.276
<i>Give it to me.</i>

53:52.489 --> 53:55.723
You'd like to stick
that thing in me, wouldn't ya?

53:55.725 --> 53:59.560
You'd like to gut me good,
wouldn't ya, boy?

54:00.496 --> 54:03.430
Well, here's your chance.

54:04.366 --> 54:06.366
Go ahead.

54:06.368 --> 54:10.837
I dare you.

54:17.245 --> 54:21.347
You didn't kill me, boy.
Big mistake!

54:21.349 --> 54:24.216
'Cause if you tell anybody
what you know,

54:24.218 --> 54:26.818
I sure as hell
am gonna kill you!

54:37.496 --> 54:39.863
<i>[ Hammering, men chatting ]</i>

54:39.865 --> 54:43.466
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>Hey, muff.</i>
Hi, tom.

54:43.468 --> 54:45.501
How you feelin'?

54:45.503 --> 54:48.504
Not so good.

54:48.506 --> 54:51.473
They treatin' you okay?

54:51.475 --> 54:55.743
It's an awful thing
that's happened, tom,

54:55.745 --> 54:58.312
and now I gotta swing for it.

54:58.314 --> 55:01.748
<i>[ Hammering continues ]</i>
[ Man ]
Give her a try.

55:03.384 --> 55:06.384
Maybe not.

55:09.789 --> 55:11.989
I'm innocent.

55:11.991 --> 55:14.591
I didn't do it.
I swear!

55:14.593 --> 55:17.694
I done a lot of crazy,
drunk things in my time.

55:17.696 --> 55:20.797
But I never killed anyone.
You gotta believe me.
I do, muff.

55:20.799 --> 55:25.267
You do?
<i>Yep, I do, muff.</i>

55:25.269 --> 55:27.569
How come?

55:27.571 --> 55:31.539
Well, I know you, muff.

55:31.541 --> 55:35.409
I mean, sure
when you get drunk,
you're awful disgusting...

55:35.411 --> 55:37.277
<i>And you smell too.</i>

55:37.279 --> 55:41.581
But I know
you wouldn't hurt a fly.

55:46.654 --> 55:50.322
Oh... muff, muff,
please don't cry. Please.

55:53.293 --> 55:55.493
You been mighty good
to me, tom.

55:55.495 --> 55:57.962
Better than anybody else
in this town,
and I'm not gonna forget it.

55:57.964 --> 56:00.264
<i>I swear I'm not.</i>

56:00.266 --> 56:03.467
Let me shake your hand, tom.

56:03.469 --> 56:06.536
<i>You'll have</i>
<i>to come through the bars.</i>
<i>Mine's too big.</i>

56:08.640 --> 56:10.773
Little hands.

56:13.477 --> 56:17.712
But I know they'd help
muff Potter a power
if'n they could.

56:25.354 --> 56:28.388
<i>[ Aunt Polly ] Tom?</i>

56:28.390 --> 56:31.456
<i>Tom? Tom!</i>

56:33.760 --> 56:38.395
Why, tom, it's not bedtime
for another hour.

56:38.397 --> 56:41.297
Are you feeling all right?

56:46.836 --> 56:50.038
You don't have a fever.

56:50.040 --> 56:53.474
What's ailing you?

56:54.810 --> 56:57.744
Aunt Polly,

56:57.746 --> 57:00.780
what if you swore an oath...

57:00.782 --> 57:03.916
Promising
not to tell somethin',

57:03.918 --> 57:08.853
but the something
you promised not to tell
needs tellin'?

57:08.855 --> 57:11.722
<i>Hmm.</i>

57:11.724 --> 57:14.758
<i>I guess you can't break</i>
<i>the oath.</i>

57:14.760 --> 57:18.628
You'd drop dead and rot.
<i>Not good.</i>

57:18.630 --> 57:22.198
And on top of that,
someone will cut your neck
with a knife.

57:22.200 --> 57:24.934
Not good at all!

57:26.671 --> 57:31.473
But if you don't tell,
somethin' worse will happen...

57:31.475 --> 57:34.676
To someone
who doesn't deserve it.

57:34.678 --> 57:40.180
<i>Tom, for as long as I</i>
<i>can remember, you have been</i>
<i>nothing but trouble to me.</i>

57:42.117 --> 57:47.152
<i>Most of the time</i>
<i>you are selfish</i>
<i>and irresponsible.</i>

57:48.855 --> 57:52.990
But you're a good boy.
You've got a good heart.

57:52.992 --> 57:57.727
And I believe you'll know
the right thing to do.

57:57.729 --> 58:00.996
And you'll do it.

58:03.800 --> 58:06.867
Just follow your heart.

58:14.008 --> 58:18.076
[ Sighs ] Muff's a goner.

58:20.013 --> 58:21.979
And you're sure,

58:21.981 --> 58:25.615
beyond any shadow of a doubt,

58:25.617 --> 58:27.883
that this is the implement...

58:27.885 --> 58:31.219
Upon which a transaction
resulting in purchase...

58:31.221 --> 58:35.889
Between yourself
and the accused, as vendee,

58:35.891 --> 58:38.892
took place?

58:38.894 --> 58:43.162
I, uh...
could you repeat the question,
please?

58:43.164 --> 58:45.264
<i>[ Gallery laughing ]</i>

58:45.266 --> 58:48.634
<i>[ Lawyer ]</i>
<i>You're sure</i>
<i>this is the knife...</i>

58:48.636 --> 58:50.902
You sold?
Sure, I'm sure!

58:50.904 --> 58:52.970
Last winter.
Aha!

58:52.972 --> 58:55.973
Last winter.

58:57.609 --> 59:01.911
And, um, is the beneficiary...

59:01.913 --> 59:06.282
<i>Of the aforementioned</i>
<i>transaction</i>
<i>present here today?</i>

59:06.284 --> 59:09.084
<i>If you're askin' me</i>
<i>about muff Potter,</i>
<i>i can tell you that he...</i>

59:09.086 --> 59:11.920
could you, please,

59:11.922 --> 59:15.256
point out
the owner of this knife?

59:15.258 --> 59:19.159
[ Chuckling ]
Are you blind?
He's sittin' right there.

59:20.996 --> 59:24.130
<i>[ Lawyer ]</i>
<i>Say the name, please.</i>

59:24.132 --> 59:28.267
Potter! Potter!
Muff Potter!

59:28.269 --> 59:31.570
<i>[ Witness ]</i>
<i>Everyone knows</i>
<i>it's muff Potter.</i>

59:31.572 --> 59:34.005
Muff Potter!

59:34.007 --> 59:35.873
Thanking you.

59:35.875 --> 59:39.809
<i>That will be all.</i>
<i>Take the witness.</i>

59:42.880 --> 59:45.113
No questions.

59:45.115 --> 59:48.883
<i>[ Gallery muttering ]</i>

59:51.287 --> 59:54.121
So I went
on up to the cemetery.

59:54.123 --> 59:57.858
I like to sit up there
and watch the stars.

59:57.860 --> 01:00:01.728
Anyway, I saw muff drunk.

01:00:01.730 --> 01:00:04.263
Real drunk and in a rage.

01:00:04.265 --> 01:00:08.267
And he lifted the knife...
And he stuck it in the doc.

01:00:08.269 --> 01:00:10.302
<i>[ Gallery murmuring ]</i>

01:00:10.304 --> 01:00:14.706
Over and over and over.

01:00:14.708 --> 01:00:17.809
'Bout four times
he stuck 'im...

01:00:17.811 --> 01:00:19.910
'Til he was dead.

01:00:23.115 --> 01:00:24.914
<i>[ Lawyer ] Take the witness.</i>

01:00:24.916 --> 01:00:29.318
No questions.
Mr. aycock,

01:00:29.320 --> 01:00:34.589
I would be obliged
if you would at least pretend
to defend Mr. Potter.

01:00:34.591 --> 01:00:37.625
<i>[ Loud chatting ]</i>

01:00:37.627 --> 01:00:40.995
<i>[ Gavel banging ] Order!</i>

01:00:40.997 --> 01:00:44.597
There will be order
in this courtroom!

01:00:46.334 --> 01:00:50.269
You may step down.

01:00:50.271 --> 01:00:52.871
<i>[ Lawyer ]</i>
<i>Thanking you,</i>
<i>your honor.</i>

01:00:52.873 --> 01:00:55.840
<i>By the oaths...</i>

01:00:55.842 --> 01:00:57.875
Of honest citizens...

01:00:57.877 --> 01:01:02.746
Whose simple word
is above suspicion,

01:01:02.748 --> 01:01:08.150
we have fastened this crime,
this awful crime,

01:01:08.152 --> 01:01:12.186
beyond all possibility
of question...

01:01:13.722 --> 01:01:15.822
Upon the unhappy prisoner.

01:01:18.092 --> 01:01:22.394
<i>Muff Potter is guilty</i>
<i>of the murder</i>
<i>of Dr. Jonas Robinson!</i>

01:01:27.367 --> 01:01:31.335
We rest our case... here.

01:01:32.905 --> 01:01:35.672
<i>[ Man ] Well said.</i>
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>That's a gift.</i>

01:01:35.674 --> 01:01:38.007
[ Gavel banging ]

01:01:38.009 --> 01:01:42.410
Counsel for the defense.

01:01:42.412 --> 01:01:46.113
Do you have a defense?

01:01:46.115 --> 01:01:49.416
<i>Indeed we do,</i>
<i>your honor!</i>
Good.

01:01:49.418 --> 01:01:54.119
The defense calls to the stand
Mr. Thomas Sawyer.

01:01:54.121 --> 01:01:57.956
Wha...
whatcha doin'?

01:02:21.714 --> 01:02:24.448
Thomas Sawyer,
do you solemnly swear
to tell the truth,

01:02:24.450 --> 01:02:29.119
the whole truth
and nothin' but the truth,
so help you God?

01:02:30.755 --> 01:02:33.155
<i>[ Tom ] I, uh...</i>

01:02:33.157 --> 01:02:36.124
I, uh...
<i>[ Judge ]</i>
<i>tom.</i>

01:02:36.126 --> 01:02:38.459
Do you swear to tell the truth?

01:02:40.296 --> 01:02:44.097
- It would certainly be
the first time.
- Stop it!

01:02:44.099 --> 01:02:45.898
I do.

01:02:45.900 --> 01:02:48.834
Then have a seat, son.

01:02:48.836 --> 01:02:54.405
<i>Mr. Sawyer, where were you</i>
<i>the twenty-eighth of this month</i>
<i>at the hour of midnight?</i>

01:02:54.407 --> 01:02:57.408
I was in the graveyard...
Sir.

01:02:57.410 --> 01:03:00.811
[ Murmuring ]
What were
you doing there?

01:03:02.881 --> 01:03:05.381
Tryin' to get rid
of warts, sir.

01:03:05.383 --> 01:03:08.717
[ Laughing ]

01:03:08.719 --> 01:03:12.487
Were you close to the grave that
muff Potter was digging up?

01:03:17.059 --> 01:03:20.160
[ Panting ]
I... I...

01:03:20.162 --> 01:03:22.362
<i>I...</i>

01:03:22.364 --> 01:03:24.731
this is a waste of time.

01:03:24.733 --> 01:03:28.501
Thomas Sawyer wouldn't know
the truth if it kicked him
in the teeth.

01:03:28.503 --> 01:03:30.836
The boy's an outright liar!

01:03:30.838 --> 01:03:33.738
I <i> was</i> there!
I <i> saw</i> the murder!

01:03:33.740 --> 01:03:37.007
Doc Robinson
wasn't stabbed four times.
He was stabbed three times.

01:03:37.009 --> 01:03:41.777
He is right!
And I ain't told that
to a soul!

01:03:44.014 --> 01:03:47.148
It wasn't muff.

01:03:47.150 --> 01:03:50.951
Muff even tried to stop it.

01:03:50.953 --> 01:03:55.388
But injun Joe
took muff's knife...

01:03:55.390 --> 01:03:58.290
And stabbed the doc.

01:03:59.893 --> 01:04:03.527
[ Sighs ] It was injun Joe.

01:04:08.333 --> 01:04:10.533
Tom!

01:04:10.535 --> 01:04:13.202
[ Gallery screaming ]
Stop right there!

01:04:22.178 --> 01:04:25.445
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Go get him! Let's go!</i>

01:04:28.149 --> 01:04:32.084
<i>Tom.</i>
<i>[ Judge ] don't just</i>
<i>stand there. Go after him!</i>

01:04:32.086 --> 01:04:34.886
All right, all right.

01:04:34.888 --> 01:04:37.121
[ Laughing, crying ]

01:04:37.123 --> 01:04:40.023
All right.
He's fine.
Tom, are you
all right?

01:04:40.025 --> 01:04:43.426
He's fine. Sit down.
Sit down.
Oh, my darling!

01:04:43.428 --> 01:04:48.097
Good job.
Yes, sir.
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>he's a brave boy.</i>

01:04:53.436 --> 01:04:57.904
<i>[ Door creaking ]</i>

01:04:57.906 --> 01:05:00.039
Hey, Joe!

01:05:00.041 --> 01:05:03.008
Gonna do some diggin'
without me?
<i>No, Joe. I was, uh...</i>

01:05:03.010 --> 01:05:07.812
I was just gettin' these tools
together in case you come back.
Oh, am I glad to see ya!

01:05:07.814 --> 01:05:10.147
I don't think
you're glad to see me.

01:05:10.149 --> 01:05:13.383
I think you was gonna go
to number two
under the cross...

01:05:13.385 --> 01:05:15.551
And get the treasure
for yourself!

01:05:15.553 --> 01:05:17.386
[ Yells ]

01:05:17.388 --> 01:05:20.288
I wouldn't cheat ya!

01:05:20.290 --> 01:05:23.725
That's right.

01:05:23.726 --> 01:05:27.161
<i>You wouldn't cheat me</i>
<i>'cause you're smart enough</i>
<i>to know if you ever did,</i>

01:05:27.997 --> 01:05:30.564
[ groans ]

01:05:30.566 --> 01:05:32.966
<i>I just might have to kill you.</i>

01:05:36.271 --> 01:05:39.038
<i>[ Aunt Polly ] Injun Joe's</i>
<i>far, far away from here.</i>
<i>Believe me, tom.</i>

01:05:39.040 --> 01:05:41.440
<i>And Mary's taking</i>
<i>the flowers as usual.</i>

01:05:41.442 --> 01:05:45.577
I'll need you and sid
to carry the jam. Tom, mind you
don't eat any on the way there.

01:05:45.579 --> 01:05:50.014
<i>[ Tom ] I ain't goin'.</i>
You're not going
to the picnic?

01:05:50.016 --> 01:05:54.985
<i>Shut your head, sid.</i>
Tom, now I know you're scared,
and rightly so.

01:05:54.987 --> 01:05:59.289
But right now you're
a glittering hero, and the whole
town'll be wantin' to see you.

01:05:59.291 --> 01:06:02.358
It's not your place
to be worrying
about that injun Joe.

01:06:02.360 --> 01:06:07.596
I hear a detective
came up from St. Louis.
They say he found a clue.

01:06:07.598 --> 01:06:11.099
Yeah, well, you can't
hang a clue for murder.

01:06:11.101 --> 01:06:13.367
Did you hear that?

01:06:13.369 --> 01:06:17.138
<i>[ Tom ] What?</i>
I thought
I heard somethin'.

01:06:17.140 --> 01:06:20.975
- Where?
- Maybe...

01:06:20.977 --> 01:06:23.177
At the front door.

01:06:23.179 --> 01:06:26.180
Well, go see, sid.

01:06:31.587 --> 01:06:34.588
<i>[ Sid ] One moment, please!</i>

01:06:36.258 --> 01:06:41.427
Oh, tom, there's
an Indian gentleman
to see you.

01:06:41.429 --> 01:06:44.463
[ Laughing ]

01:06:45.666 --> 01:06:48.599
Tom! Wha...
tom! Sid!

01:06:50.569 --> 01:06:53.336
[ Sighs ]

01:06:59.410 --> 01:07:01.643
[ Leaves rustling ]

01:07:01.645 --> 01:07:04.245
[ Gasps ]

01:07:16.758 --> 01:07:20.359
[ Panting ]

01:07:39.512 --> 01:07:42.079
[ Screams ] Shh.

01:07:42.081 --> 01:07:44.514
<i>You scared?</i>

01:07:44.516 --> 01:07:46.582
You should be.

01:07:46.584 --> 01:07:49.518
Huck, what are you doin'?

01:07:49.520 --> 01:07:52.721
Remember this?
Yeah.
But, huck...

01:07:52.723 --> 01:07:57.225
according to this,
you should be dead
and rottin' right about now.

01:07:57.227 --> 01:08:01.629
I had to help muff.

01:08:01.631 --> 01:08:04.398
Not helpin' him
would've been wrong.

01:08:04.400 --> 01:08:07.267
I know, but...
You swore an oath, tom.

01:08:07.269 --> 01:08:11.604
Don't that mean anything to ya?

01:08:11.606 --> 01:08:15.407
Yeah, of course it does.

01:08:15.409 --> 01:08:19.243
It's just...

01:08:19.246 --> 01:08:22.180
it just felt like
the right thing to do.

01:08:23.716 --> 01:08:26.649
Huck, it was
the right thing to do.
No!

01:08:26.652 --> 01:08:30.720
You swore an oath, tom.
You swore!

01:08:30.721 --> 01:08:33.322
What was I supposed to do, huh?

01:08:33.323 --> 01:08:35.557
Just lay back
and let muff Potter swing?
You tell me, huck!

01:08:35.559 --> 01:08:39.359
You know you ain't never
been in more trouble
than you are right now!

01:08:39.362 --> 01:08:44.264
- Injun Joe's gonna kill you.
- You think I don't know that?

01:08:44.265 --> 01:08:48.801
Just don't expect me
to stick around and save
your little neck this time.

01:08:48.803 --> 01:08:51.303
I don't.

01:08:51.305 --> 01:08:53.805
Good.
'Cause I ain't goin' to.

01:08:53.807 --> 01:08:56.674
Then why'd ya come back?

01:08:56.676 --> 01:08:59.143
I don't know.

01:08:59.145 --> 01:09:01.879
To tell you to be careful.

01:09:01.881 --> 01:09:04.514
I've been to your funeral once.

01:09:04.515 --> 01:09:07.550
<i>I ain't goin' again.</i>

01:09:13.557 --> 01:09:15.723
[ Sighs ]

01:09:16.459 --> 01:09:19.292
Huck! Hey, huck!

01:09:21.296 --> 01:09:23.529
<i>Muff Potter's my friend.</i>

01:09:25.600 --> 01:09:30.135
When a friend's in trouble,
you can't run away.

01:09:44.517 --> 01:09:47.684
<i>If you go to the crossroads</i>
<i>and you listen to the wind,</i>

01:09:47.685 --> 01:09:51.821
it'll tell you all the important
things that are gonna happen
to ya in the next twelve months.

01:09:51.823 --> 01:09:55.858
<i>Now, you may be wantin'</i>
<i>to tell, you may</i>
<i>be wantin' to fuss...</i>

01:09:55.860 --> 01:09:58.727
[ girls laughing ]

01:10:07.270 --> 01:10:10.204
[ Gasps ] Hmm?

01:10:14.810 --> 01:10:18.812
<i>Come back here.</i>
<i>I'm gonna get you!</i>

01:10:18.814 --> 01:10:22.215
<i>[ Aunt Polly ]</i>
<i>Tom, don't...</i>
<i>sid, now don't...</i>

01:10:24.385 --> 01:10:27.219
[ tom ]
Come back here!
I'm not done with you yet!

01:10:33.260 --> 01:10:36.461
I sow hemp seed;
And he who is
to be my husband,

01:10:36.463 --> 01:10:40.531
let him come and harrow it.

01:10:40.533 --> 01:10:43.600
Look into the mirror,
and you shall see
the form of your husband.

01:10:43.602 --> 01:10:46.402
[ Girls giggling ]

01:10:47.738 --> 01:10:51.372
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Come and get some pie, gals.</i>

01:10:55.811 --> 01:11:00.280
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>Come on, sid! Come here.</i>
<i>Got another spider for ya!</i>

01:11:00.282 --> 01:11:02.582
<i>[ Sid ]</i>
<i>Na-na-na-na.</i>

01:11:02.584 --> 01:11:04.850
Hey, Becky.

01:11:07.354 --> 01:11:09.520
Oh, no!

01:11:09.522 --> 01:11:11.622
What? What'd I do?
We're
gonna be married.

01:11:11.624 --> 01:11:14.524
Huh?
You needn't look
so disappointed.

01:11:14.526 --> 01:11:16.992
I don't like it
any better than you do!

01:11:19.329 --> 01:11:21.896
[ Sighs ]

01:11:21.898 --> 01:11:24.465
<i>[ Muff ]</i>
<i>Every one of 'em was dead.</i>

01:11:24.467 --> 01:11:27.701
<i>And every one of 'em...</i>
<i>Was smilin'.</i>

01:11:27.703 --> 01:11:30.637
[ Children gasp ]

01:11:30.639 --> 01:11:34.007
Well, I run out of stories.

01:11:34.009 --> 01:11:38.744
How 'bout we go
look at the cave?
[ Cheering ]

01:11:40.814 --> 01:11:44.916
Come on, boys and girls,
let's go look at that cave!

01:12:30.796 --> 01:12:34.564
<i>[ Judge ]</i>
<i>Everybody stay together.</i>
<i>No wandering off!</i>

01:12:34.566 --> 01:12:39.635
<i>So he said, "me?"</i>
<i>In a silly voice.</i>
<i>So I said...</i>

01:12:39.637 --> 01:12:42.404
hello, sir.
This truly is
a wondrous place.

01:12:42.406 --> 01:12:46.074
God's own cathedral,
your honor.
Well put,
Mr. Potter.

01:12:46.076 --> 01:12:47.909
<i>[ Judge ] Be careful, Rebecca.</i>

01:12:47.911 --> 01:12:51.712
I will.
<i>You children</i>
<i>stay to the forechambers.</i>

01:12:51.714 --> 01:12:54.347
<i>[ Muff ]</i>
<i>You heard the judge.</i>
<i>Now, listen to him.</i>

01:12:54.349 --> 01:12:57.550
"Be careful, Rebecca.
Stay close to the forechamber,
Rebecca."

01:12:57.552 --> 01:13:00.653
I'll go where I please.

01:13:07.494 --> 01:13:10.528
I dare ya.

01:13:17.402 --> 01:13:21.937
¶ Ring around the Rosie
pocketful of posies ¶

01:13:21.939 --> 01:13:26.107
<i>¶ ashes, ashes</i>
<i>we all fall down ¶¶</i>

01:13:37.352 --> 01:13:39.552
it's beautiful.

01:13:39.554 --> 01:13:44.557
<i>I've been here a million times.</i>
<i>Satan's cathedral.</i>

01:13:44.559 --> 01:13:49.128
Well, I'll find a cavern
you haven't been to,
and I'll name it myself!

01:13:50.531 --> 01:13:53.365
[ Whispering, mimicking Becky ]
I'll name it myself.

01:14:14.720 --> 01:14:18.054
<i>[ Muff ]</i>
<i>Come on, move it. Come on.</i>
<i>[ Child ] I'm here.</i>

01:14:18.056 --> 01:14:22.558
Stragglers, move on.
That's it.
<i>[ Boy ] Good-bye, muff.</i>

01:14:22.560 --> 01:14:24.760
Yeah.
[ Clears throat ]

01:14:26.396 --> 01:14:30.398
Yeah, that's the last
of 'em.
Looks like
that about does it.

01:14:30.400 --> 01:14:34.435
[ Chuckles ]
Here, I don't mind
if I do.

01:14:34.437 --> 01:14:37.003
I don't mind
if you do, either.
[ Laughing ]

01:14:39.941 --> 01:14:43.709
Excuse me, judge.
I was wondering
if you'd seen tom.

01:14:43.711 --> 01:14:47.012
<i>He was with my Rebecca.</i>
<i>They were chasing each other</i>
<i>around in the back of the cave.</i>

01:14:47.014 --> 01:14:49.047
<i>I'm assuming they came out</i>
<i>with everybody else.</i>

01:14:49.049 --> 01:14:52.116
What is it, sheriff?
What's wrong?

01:14:52.118 --> 01:14:55.486
I was out makin' my rounds,
and I seen
the tavern door open.

01:14:55.488 --> 01:15:00.557
So I went on inside,
and there he was lying there
deader than a mackerel.

01:15:00.559 --> 01:15:03.526
Emmett. Big ol' knife hole
in his back.

01:15:03.528 --> 01:15:06.529
<i>[ Sheriff ]</i>
<i>Ain't but one man</i>
<i>throw a knife like that.</i>

01:15:13.137 --> 01:15:18.807
Look at this one.
This one's beautiful too.
I'll name this one.

01:15:18.809 --> 01:15:22.010
We call it Aladdin's palace.

01:15:22.012 --> 01:15:23.611
Hello!

01:15:23.613 --> 01:15:26.180
<i>[ Echoing ] Hello!</i>

01:15:26.182 --> 01:15:29.683
<i>[ Tom ] Hello!</i>

01:15:30.952 --> 01:15:33.052
Hello?

01:15:33.054 --> 01:15:35.554
Hello!

01:15:35.556 --> 01:15:38.690
Hello!
Hello!

01:15:38.692 --> 01:15:41.059
Hello!
Hello!

01:15:41.061 --> 01:15:42.960
<i>[ Echoing ] Hello!</i>

01:15:42.962 --> 01:15:46.196
Hello! Hello!
<i>[ Rocks landsliding ]</i>

01:15:46.198 --> 01:15:50.800
Hello! Hello!
No.
No, Becky, stop!

01:15:50.802 --> 01:15:54.103
Stop, Becky, stop!
Don't tell me
what to do!

01:15:54.105 --> 01:15:55.904
<i>[ Echoing ] Tell me what to do.</i>

01:15:57.607 --> 01:15:59.607
Becky!

01:16:12.754 --> 01:16:16.489
<i>[ Rocks landsliding ]</i>

01:16:18.593 --> 01:16:22.561
<i>[ Judge ] Gentlemen, my</i>
<i>daughter Rebecca and tom Sawyer</i>
<i>are both lost in the caves.</i>

01:16:22.563 --> 01:16:25.964
<i>And injun Joe has come back</i>
<i>to take his revenge on tom.</i>

01:16:25.966 --> 01:16:30.568
Now, be on your guard.
Injun Joe
has already killed twice.

01:16:30.570 --> 01:16:33.771
The sheriff and I believe
that he will not hesitate
to kill again.

01:16:33.773 --> 01:16:36.640
Judge? Judge.

01:16:36.642 --> 01:16:40.109
Judge, I'd like to help ya.

01:16:41.245 --> 01:16:44.746
All right, muff.
Let's go!

01:16:44.748 --> 01:16:47.014
[ Shouting ]

01:17:11.740 --> 01:17:14.640
This way.

01:17:51.577 --> 01:17:54.744
What's this cavern called, tom?

01:17:55.713 --> 01:17:57.979
I don't know.

01:18:07.756 --> 01:18:10.756
[ Both gasping ]

01:18:13.961 --> 01:18:17.295
It's just rock.

01:18:21.934 --> 01:18:23.934
<i>[ Muff ]</i>
<i>Judge!</i>
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>any luck?</i>

01:18:23.936 --> 01:18:26.803
<i>Over here, judge.</i>

01:18:26.805 --> 01:18:29.305
What is it, muff?
There's been
a cave-in.

01:18:29.307 --> 01:18:32.374
There are other ways out.
Okay? N-now...

01:18:32.376 --> 01:18:34.642
[ judge ] Becky!

01:18:42.318 --> 01:18:45.952
I, I think we're gonna be
stuck here forever.

01:18:45.954 --> 01:18:51.290
Don't worry, Becky.
I'm gonna get you outta here.
I promise.

01:18:51.292 --> 01:18:55.460
<i>[ Rock falling ]</i>

01:19:01.367 --> 01:19:04.935
Run, Becky, run!

01:19:17.382 --> 01:19:20.015
- Hah!
- [ Becky screams ]

01:19:20.017 --> 01:19:22.217
[ Ripping sound ]

01:19:26.056 --> 01:19:28.189
This way! This way!

01:19:30.293 --> 01:19:33.260
Through here.
Through here.
Go! Go!

01:19:33.262 --> 01:19:36.062
Hurry, hurry!
Go! Go!

01:19:36.064 --> 01:19:39.298
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>Becky! Go, go.</i>

01:19:39.300 --> 01:19:43.969
[ Tom ]
Hurry up.
<i>[ Becky ] Tom!</i>

01:19:43.971 --> 01:19:46.338
<i>[ Becky ] Tom!</i>

01:19:46.340 --> 01:19:48.939
Becky.

01:19:52.044 --> 01:19:55.545
[ Panting ]
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>I think we lost him.</i>

01:20:04.088 --> 01:20:06.254
[ Whimpering ]

01:20:21.037 --> 01:20:23.404
[ Screaming ]

01:20:32.581 --> 01:20:36.950
<i>[ Tom ]</i>
<i>It's one-eyed murrell.</i>

01:20:36.952 --> 01:20:40.353
<i>He must've been</i>
<i>hiding here when</i>
<i>the army came to get him.</i>

01:20:40.355 --> 01:20:45.124
<i>Looks like he got lost</i>
<i>and slowly... died.</i>

01:20:45.126 --> 01:20:47.159
Come on.

01:20:47.161 --> 01:20:49.194
Please be careful.

01:20:49.196 --> 01:20:54.165
This way, Becky.
<i>Not so loud, tom.</i>
<i>He'll hear us.</i>

01:20:56.602 --> 01:21:00.170
<i>[ Tom ] Number two</i>
<i>under the cross!</i>
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

01:21:09.614 --> 01:21:11.880
Becky, look!

01:21:19.489 --> 01:21:22.857
Go on.
I'm right behind you.

01:21:28.230 --> 01:21:30.330
Tom, come on.

01:21:30.332 --> 01:21:33.299
Find your father.
Bring him back.

01:21:34.402 --> 01:21:38.237
It's dangerous.
Hurry!

01:22:00.427 --> 01:22:02.560
[ Gasps ]

01:22:08.634 --> 01:22:12.935
<i>Looks like I got it all!</i>
<i>The treasure... and you!</i>

01:22:13.604 --> 01:22:16.438
[ Screams ]

01:22:32.021 --> 01:22:34.021
<i>Hey!</i>

01:22:49.404 --> 01:22:51.704
I know you.

01:22:55.942 --> 01:22:57.975
Huck?

01:22:59.078 --> 01:23:02.512
You're pap finn's boy.

01:23:02.514 --> 01:23:05.114
Blueberry!

01:23:05.116 --> 01:23:07.416
Huckleberry.

01:23:09.420 --> 01:23:13.388
Your daddy
was the best knife fighter
on the Mississippi.

01:23:13.390 --> 01:23:16.257
Did he teach you?

01:23:16.259 --> 01:23:18.292
He taught me.

01:23:18.294 --> 01:23:20.127
Ah.

01:23:21.597 --> 01:23:25.298
Then let's see what you got,
river trash.
[ Laughing ]

01:23:25.300 --> 01:23:28.301
I ain't river trash!
Come on!

01:23:28.303 --> 01:23:31.070
[ Grunts ]

01:23:35.042 --> 01:23:37.208
You got guts, boy!

01:23:37.210 --> 01:23:40.978
And in a minute,
they're gonna be on the ground.

01:23:40.980 --> 01:23:44.114
Let's see you hit this!

01:23:44.116 --> 01:23:46.449
[ Yells ]

01:24:04.735 --> 01:24:07.268
[ Screaming ]

01:24:31.026 --> 01:24:35.060
So, why'd you come back, huck?

01:24:36.463 --> 01:24:39.664
When a friend's in trouble,
you don't run away.

01:24:48.707 --> 01:24:52.709
I guess
injun Joe got his treasure.

01:24:52.711 --> 01:24:55.378
No, no, he didn't.

01:24:58.383 --> 01:25:03.318
The chest,
I couldn't lift it.
It was too heavy.

01:25:03.320 --> 01:25:07.322
I had to dump out
all the coins.

01:25:14.430 --> 01:25:16.730
<i>[ Muff ]</i>
<i>Here comes our hero!</i>
<i>There he is!</i>

01:25:16.732 --> 01:25:19.165
Gimme your hand.

01:25:19.167 --> 01:25:21.467
[ People laughing, cheering ]

01:25:22.770 --> 01:25:25.604
It's all right.
Come on out.

01:25:25.606 --> 01:25:31.108
Bring 'em over here.
[ Laughing ]
You're a good boy!

01:25:31.110 --> 01:25:34.244
Three cheers. Three cheers
for the richest boys
in Hannibal.

01:25:34.246 --> 01:25:40.115
Hip, hip, hooray!
Hip, hip, hooray!
Hip, hip, hooray!

01:25:40.117 --> 01:25:42.416
Thank you, judge.
Thank you.

01:25:45.254 --> 01:25:48.321
Young man,
what's to become of you?

01:25:48.323 --> 01:25:51.123
Have you begun to think
about your future?

01:25:51.125 --> 01:25:54.159
No, ma'am.
I never really
much had a future.

01:25:54.161 --> 01:25:58.362
Well, you've got one now.
And you best begin!

01:26:01.867 --> 01:26:04.701
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>You are indeed our hero, tom!</i>

01:26:04.703 --> 01:26:09.505
<i>You're a hero, tom.</i>
<i>You made the front page!</i>

01:26:09.507 --> 01:26:12.140
Congratulations.
So proud.

01:26:15.411 --> 01:26:18.711
<i>Fine boy, tom.</i>
<i>Mighty nice.</i>

01:26:20.648 --> 01:26:23.882
Hannibal's proud
of our fine young man.

01:26:35.261 --> 01:26:37.527
[ Laughing ]

01:26:49.741 --> 01:26:51.907
Huck! Hey, huck!

01:26:53.510 --> 01:26:58.245
<i>Hey, who are you?</i>
<i>What are you doin' here?</i>

01:26:58.247 --> 01:27:00.814
- Huck?
- What do you think?

01:27:00.816 --> 01:27:04.484
Well, I think one of us
has lost his mind.

01:27:04.486 --> 01:27:08.654
The widow Douglas
is gonna adopt me.

01:27:08.656 --> 01:27:12.591
The widow?

01:27:21.401 --> 01:27:24.769
You're givin' all this up,
move into town?

01:27:24.771 --> 01:27:27.772
Why not?
Why not?
I'll tell you why not.

01:27:27.774 --> 01:27:30.407
Huck finn goin' to church?
Huck finn goin' to school?

01:27:30.409 --> 01:27:34.377
I start
tomorrow mornin'.
I gotta sit down.

01:27:34.379 --> 01:27:36.278
Huck?

01:27:36.280 --> 01:27:40.515
<i>Huck,</i>
<i>say it ain't so.</i>
I gotta get goin'.

01:27:40.517 --> 01:27:42.316
I promised the widow
I'd take her
to the church social.

01:27:42.318 --> 01:27:45.485
Church social?

01:27:45.487 --> 01:27:47.620
All right, that's it!
That tears it!

01:27:47.622 --> 01:27:52.291
I ain't gonna stop ya.
I'm stayin' here.
Somebody's gotta carry on.

01:27:54.228 --> 01:27:58.230
Suit yourself, tom.
I hope things work out for ya.

01:27:58.232 --> 01:28:01.299
Nights out here get awful cold.

01:28:01.301 --> 01:28:04.502
Well, you know where to find me
if you change your mind.

01:28:04.504 --> 01:28:07.805
And you know where to find me.

01:28:17.816 --> 01:28:20.950
Huck!

01:28:20.952 --> 01:28:23.319
Huck, wait for me!

01:28:23.321 --> 01:28:27.690
You comin' along?

01:28:27.692 --> 01:28:32.628
I guess I got to.
Somebody's gotta look out
for ya.

01:28:32.630 --> 01:28:36.465
Civilization can be
a pretty dangerous place.

01:28:36.467 --> 01:28:38.867
So...

01:28:38.869 --> 01:28:42.303
You ready to go put
some gray hairs
on your aunt's head?

01:28:42.305 --> 01:28:44.772
Whatcha got in mind?

01:28:44.774 --> 01:28:47.741
